            <head>THE FIRST
Part of the <normalised orig="priuiledges" auto="true">privileges</normalised>
of a Christian.</head>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Question.<lb/>
WHat is your Name?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. N or M.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. Who <normalised orig="gaue" auto="true">gave</normalised> you that<lb/>
                  <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic><notvariant>nam</notvariant>*</sic>
                     <corr>name</corr>
                  </choice>?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. My Godfathers and<lb/>
my Godmothers in my <normalised orig="Baptisme" auto="true">Baptism</normalised>;<lb/>
wherein I was made a member of<lb/>
Christ, a <normalised orig="childe" auto="true">child</normalised> of God, and an inheritor<lb/>
of the <normalised orig="kingdome" auto="true">kingdom</normalised> of <normalised orig="heauen" auto="true">heaven</normalised>.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. Why was your name <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic><notvariant>giu</notvariant>*n</sic>
                     <corr><normalised orig="giuen" auto="true">given</normalised></corr>
                  </choice> to<lb/>
you in your <normalised orig="Baptisme" auto="true">Baptism</normalised>?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. First, to <normalised orig="signifie" auto="true">signify</normalised> that then and<lb/>
not before, I <normalised orig="obtaine" auto="true">obtain</normalised> a name and account<lb/>
with God, to be <normalised orig="knowne" auto="true">known</normalised> for his,<lb/>
and to be as on record in his <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic><normalised orig="Bo" auto="true">By</normalised>*<notvariant>ke</notvariant></sic>
                     <corr><normalised orig="Booke" auto="true">Book</normalised></corr>
                  </choice>,<lb/>
enrolled a citizen with his Saints,<lb/>
when renouncing what formerly I<lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <fw type="pageNum">A4</fw>
                  <pb n="1"/>
                  <lb/>
<normalised orig="haue" auto="true">have</normalised> <normalised orig="beene" auto="true">been</normalised>, I betake my <normalised orig="selfe" auto="true">self</normalised> to his<lb/>
<normalised orig="seruice" auto="true">service</normalised>.<lb/>
Secondly, that so oft as I remember<lb/>
my name, I should together call to<lb/>
<normalised orig="minde" auto="true">mind</normalised> the <normalised orig="couenant" auto="true">covenant</normalised> made in my <normalised orig="baptisme" auto="true">baptism</normalised>,<lb/>
and what <normalised orig="dutie" auto="true">duty</normalised> I therein promised<lb/>
<normalised orig="vnto" auto="true">unto</normalised> God.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. If we now first come into account<lb/>
with God when we are <normalised orig="baptized" auto="true">baptised</normalised>, what<lb/>
then are we all of our <normalised orig="selues" auto="true">selves</normalised> in our <normalised orig="naturall" auto="true">natural</normalised><lb/>
condition?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. We are all borne in <normalised orig="sinne" auto="true">sin</normalised>, children<lb/>
of wrath, <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic><notvariant>slau</notvariant>*s</sic>
                     <corr><normalised orig="slaues" auto="true">slaves</normalised></corr>
                  </choice> of the <normalised orig="deuill" auto="true">devil</normalised>, <normalised orig="subiect" auto="true">subject</normalised><lb/>
to all manner punishments both<lb/>
of <normalised orig="soule" auto="true">soul</normalised> and <normalised orig="bodie" auto="true">body</normalised> in this life, and<lb/>
when death comes, to <normalised orig="eternall" auto="true">eternal</normalised> damnation<lb/>
in hell fire.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. How did we become thus <normalised orig="sinfull" auto="true">sinful</normalised><lb/>
                  <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>an*</sic>
                     <corr>and</corr>
                  </choice> miserable?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. Not by our first creation: for God<lb/>
made man <normalised orig="iust" auto="true">just</normalised> and righteous, but by<lb/>
our father <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>Adam*</sic>
                     <corr>Adams</corr>
                  </choice> <normalised orig="infidelitie" auto="true">infidelity</normalised> and disobedience,<lb/>
in eating the forbidden<lb/>
<normalised orig="fruite" auto="true">fruit</normalised>.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What <normalised orig="meanes" auto="true">means</normalised> is there of our <normalised orig="deliuerance" auto="true">deliverance</normalised><lb/>
from this damnable estate?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. No other but in <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>Ie*us</sic>
                     <corr><normalised orig="Iesus" auto="true">Jesus</normalised></corr>
                  </choice> Christ<lb/>
alone the <normalised orig="Sonne" auto="true">Son</normalised> of God: and the <normalised orig="couenant" auto="true">covenant</normalised><lb/>
of grace and <normalised orig="mercie" auto="true">mercy</normalised> which he<lb/>
                  <pb n="2"/>
                  <lb/>
<normalised orig="maketh" auto="true">makes</normalised> with <normalised orig="vs" auto="true">us</normalised> in our <normalised orig="baptisme" auto="true">baptism</normalised>.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What benefit <normalised orig="haue" auto="true">have</normalised> we by our<lb/>
<normalised orig="baptisme" auto="true">baptism</normalised>?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. Wee <normalised orig="inioy" auto="true">enjoy</normalised> hereby, (as in the<lb/>
first <normalised orig="answere" auto="true">answer</normalised> is before <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic><normalised orig="shewe" auto="true">show</normalised>*</sic>
                     <corr><normalised orig="shewed" auto="true">showed</normalised></corr>
                  </choice>) a three<lb/>
fold <normalised orig="priuiledge" auto="true">privilege</normalised> wherein a Christian<lb/>
man <normalised orig="goeth" auto="true">goes</normalised> beyond all others in the<lb/>
world.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
         </div>
         <div>
            <head>The <normalised orig="Priuiledge" auto="true">Privilege</normalised>.</head>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What is the first <normalised orig="priuiledge" auto="true">privilege</normalised>?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. The first is, that I thus become<lb/>
a member of Christ &amp; of his Church,<lb/>
one of the number and <normalised orig="societie" auto="true">society</normalised> of his<lb/>
people.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What is the benefit of such my<lb/>
being in Christ?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. An holy communion <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>an*</sic>
                     <corr>and</corr>
                  </choice> fellowship,<lb/>
and that first with Christ <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic><notvariant>himse</notvariant>*<notvariant>fe</notvariant></sic>
                     <corr><normalised orig="himselfe" auto="true">himself</normalised></corr>
                  </choice>
                  <lb/>
for <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>hi*</sic>
                     <corr>his</corr>
                  </choice> <normalised orig="righteousnesse" auto="true">righteousness</normalised>, <normalised orig="merite" auto="true">merit</normalised> and<lb/>
obedience, for my <normalised orig="iustification" auto="true">justification</normalised>, pardon<lb/>
and sanctification thereby.<lb/>
Secondly, with his Church, to <normalised orig="bee" auto="true">be</normalised><lb/>
                  <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic><normalised orig="ioy" auto="true">joy</normalised>*ed</sic>
                     <corr><normalised orig="ioyned" auto="true">joined</normalised></corr>
                  </choice> hereunto, and to <normalised orig="enioy" auto="true">enjoy</normalised> a right<lb/>
and <normalised orig="freedome" auto="true">freedom</normalised> in all the graces and benefits<lb/>
which he <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> bestowed thereon.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
         </div>
         <div>
            <head>The second <normalised orig="Priuiledge" auto="true">Privilege</normalised>.</head>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What is the <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic><notvariant>secon</notvariant>*</sic>
                     <corr>second</corr>
                  </choice> <normalised orig="priuiledge" auto="true">privilege</normalised>?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. That I am thus a child of God<lb/>
                  <pb n="3"/>
                  <lb/>
through adoption and grace.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What are the <normalised orig="signes" auto="true">signs</normalised> of such my<lb/>
adoption, whereby I may know the<lb/>
same?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. First, if I can <normalised orig="goe" auto="true">go</normalised> to God in the<lb/>
name of Christ, with a child-like confidence<lb/>
and comfortable <normalised orig="boldnesse" auto="true">boldness</normalised>, as<lb/>
to my father in <normalised orig="heartie" auto="true">hearty</normalised> and <normalised orig="feruent" auto="true">fervent</normalised><lb/>
prayer.<lb/>
Secondly, if I <normalised orig="finde" auto="true">find</normalised> in my heart the<lb/>
same affection to God which a <normalised orig="dutifull" auto="true">dutiful</normalised><lb/>
<normalised orig="childe" auto="true">child</normalised> ought to <normalised orig="haue" auto="true">have</normalised> to his father, with<lb/>
such <normalised orig="loue" auto="true">love</normalised>, <normalised orig="feare" auto="true">fear</normalised> and <normalised orig="thankefulnesse" auto="true">thankfulness</normalised><lb/>
<normalised orig="vnto" auto="true">unto</normalised> him.<lb/>
Thirdly, if I <normalised orig="conforme" auto="true">conform</normalised> my <normalised orig="selfe" auto="true">self</normalised> in<lb/>
obedience to his will, and <normalised orig="endeuour" auto="true">endeavour</normalised><lb/>
to <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>f*me</sic>
                     <corr><normalised orig="forme" auto="true">form</normalised></corr>
                  </choice> my <normalised orig="conuersation" auto="true">conversation</normalised> in <normalised orig="holinesse" auto="true">holiness</normalised><lb/>
like <normalised orig="vnto" auto="true">unto</normalised> him, as an ingenious <normalised orig="childe" auto="true">child</normalised><lb/>
<normalised orig="striues" auto="true">strives</normalised> to imitate his father.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
         </div>
         <div>
            <head>The third <normalised orig="Priuiledge" auto="true">Privilege</normalised>.</head>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What is the third <normalised orig="Priuiledge" auto="true">Privilege</normalised>?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. This <normalised orig="followeth" auto="true">follows</normalised> of the former,<lb/>
that being a <normalised orig="sonne" auto="true">son</normalised>, I am also an<lb/>
<normalised orig="heire" auto="true">heir</normalised>, <normalised orig="euen" auto="true">even</normalised> an <normalised orig="heire" auto="true">heir</normalised> of God, and <normalised orig="coheire" auto="false">coheir</normalised><lb/>
with <choice ana="print-error">
                     <sic><notvariant>Chiist</notvariant></sic>
                     <corr>Christ</corr>
                  </choice>, and <normalised orig="haue" auto="true">have</normalised> right of an<lb/>
inheritance by him.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What manner of inheritance is<lb/>
this?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. It is the inheritance of a <normalised orig="kingdome" auto="true">kingdom</normalised>,<lb/>
                  <pb n="4"/>
                  <lb/>
and this <normalised orig="immortall" auto="true">immortal</normalised> and <normalised orig="vndefiled" auto="true">undefiled</normalised>,<lb/>
and which <normalised orig="withereth" auto="true">withers</normalised> not, <normalised orig="reserued" auto="true">reserved</normalised><lb/>
in <normalised orig="heauen" auto="true">heaven</normalised> for <normalised orig="vs" auto="true">us</normalised>.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What <normalised orig="learne" auto="true">learn</normalised> we from the consideration<lb/>
of these <normalised orig="Priuiledges" auto="true">Privileges</normalised>?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. First, to <normalised orig="magnifie" auto="true">magnify</normalised> God in such<lb/>
infinite <normalised orig="mercie" auto="true">mercy</normalised>, as of <normalised orig="heires" auto="true">heirs</normalised> of corruption<lb/>
and death, to beget <normalised orig="vs" auto="true">us</normalised> <normalised orig="againe" auto="true">again</normalised> to<lb/>
a <normalised orig="liuely" auto="true">lively</normalised> hope of such an <normalised orig="immortall" auto="true">immortal</normalised> inheritance.<lb/>
Secondly, that we <normalised orig="walke" auto="true">walk</normalised> worthy<lb/>
the Lord and his high and holy calling,<lb/>
to please him in all things, and to<lb/>
count it a most <normalised orig="vnbeseeming" auto="true">unbeseeming</normalised> debasing<lb/>
of our <normalised orig="selues" auto="true">selves</normalised>, to <normalised orig="seeke" auto="true">seek</normalised> the fellowship<lb/>
of the world, and to <normalised orig="minde" auto="true">mind</normalised> earthly<lb/>
things.<lb/>
Thirdly, yet to know that in the<lb/>
things we <normalised orig="doe" auto="true">do</normalised>, we merit not this<lb/>
<normalised orig="kingdome" auto="true">kingdom</normalised>, which as here we see is an<lb/>
inheritance, and is <normalised orig="giuen" auto="true">given</normalised> <normalised orig="vs" auto="true">us</normalised> in the<lb/>
right of <normalised orig="sonnes" auto="true">sons</normalised> through Christ from<lb/>
the first time of our new birth, (as the<lb/>
first borne amongst men is <normalised orig="heire" auto="true">heir</normalised>, from<lb/>
the very moment of his birth) and not<lb/>
for our obedience sake.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
         </div>
         <div>
            <head>The second part, concerning the
duties of a Christian.</head>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What did your Godfathers and<lb/>
                  <pb n="5"/>
                  <lb/>
Godmothers promise for you in <normalised orig="Baptisme" auto="true">Baptism</normalised>?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. They did promise and vow three<lb/>
things in my name: first, that I should<lb/>
forsake the <normalised orig="diuell" auto="true">devil</normalised> and all his <normalised orig="workes" auto="true">works</normalised>,<lb/>
the <normalised orig="pompes" auto="true">pomps</normalised> and vanities of this wicked<lb/>
world, and all the <normalised orig="sinfull" auto="true">sinful</normalised> lusts of<lb/>
the flesh.<lb/>
Secondly, that I should <normalised orig="beleeue" auto="true">believe</normalised> all<lb/>
the Articles of the Christian faith.<lb/>
Thirdly, that I should <normalised orig="keepe" auto="true">keep</normalised> Gods<lb/>
holy will and <normalised orig="commandements" auto="true">commandments</normalised> and<lb/>
<normalised orig="walke" auto="true">walk</normalised> in the same all the <normalised orig="dayes" auto="true">days</normalised> of my<lb/>
life.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. <normalised orig="Doe" auto="true">Do</normalised> not you <normalised orig="thinke" auto="true">think</normalised> that you are<lb/>
bound to <normalised orig="beleeue" auto="true">believe</normalised> and to do as they <normalised orig="haue" auto="true">have</normalised><lb/>
promised for you?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. Yes verily, and by Gods <normalised orig="helpe" auto="true">help</normalised> so<lb/>
I will: and I heartily <normalised orig="thanke" auto="true">thank</normalised> our <normalised orig="heauenly" auto="true">heavenly</normalised><lb/>
father, that he <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> called me to<lb/>
this state of  <choice ana="typeset-error">
                     <sic/>
                     <corr><normalised orig="saluation" auto="true">salvation</normalised></corr>
                  </choice>, through <normalised orig="Iesus" auto="true">Jesus</normalised><lb/>
Christ our <normalised orig="Sauiour" auto="true">Saviour</normalised>: and I pray God<lb/>
to <normalised orig="giue" auto="true">give</normalised> me his grace that I may continue<lb/>
in <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>th*</sic>
                     <corr>the</corr>
                  </choice> same <normalised orig="vnto" auto="true">unto</normalised> my <normalised orig="liues" auto="true">lives</normalised> end.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. How are you bound to <normalised orig="performe" auto="true">perform</normalised><lb/>
these duties?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. Not by an <normalised orig="ordinarie" auto="true">ordinary</normalised> bond, but by<lb/>
a <normalised orig="solemne" auto="true">solemn</normalised> vow and oath hereof, which<lb/>
I must therefore <notvariant>holily</notvariant> <normalised orig="obserue" auto="true">observe</normalised>, as the<lb/>
                  <pb n="6"/>
                  <lb/>
                  <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>*<notvariant>ondition</notvariant></sic>
                     <corr>condition</corr>
                  </choice> on my part <normalised orig="couenanted" auto="true">covenanted</normalised>, or<lb/>
                  <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>*<notvariant>lse</notvariant></sic>
                     <corr>else</corr>
                  </choice> <normalised orig="neuer" auto="true">never</normalised> expect performance of life<lb/>
and <normalised orig="saluation" auto="true">salvation</normalised> from God.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. But more specially, what be those<lb/>
duties contained in the former promise<lb/>
which we <normalised orig="haue" auto="true">have</normalised> thus vowed?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. They are as is said three, first, Repentance,<lb/>
secondly, Faith, thirdly, Obedience.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
         </div>
         <div>
            <head>Of Repentance.</head>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q.What is repentance which is first<lb/>
promised?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. It is a turning <normalised orig="vnto" auto="true">unto</normalised> God from<lb/>
the <normalised orig="deuill" auto="true">devil</normalised>, whom I thus forsake and renounce,<lb/>
with all <normalised orig="sinnes" auto="true">sins</normalised> which are his<lb/>
<normalised orig="workes" auto="true">works</normalised>; and that not <normalised orig="onely" auto="true">only</normalised> for the<lb/>
greatest and most notorious, but for<lb/>
the least, to the very thoughts and<lb/>
lusts hereof, and the vanities of the<lb/>
world: and the doing of that which is<lb/>
good and right before him.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>*<normalised orig="oe" auto="true">o</normalised></sic>
                     <corr><normalised orig="doe" auto="true">do</normalised></corr>
                  </choice> you <normalised orig="meane" auto="true">mean</normalised> by the vanities<lb/>
of the world?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. All those things, whether pleasure<lb/>
and delights or <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>o*<notvariant>herwi</notvariant>*e</sic>
                     <corr>otherwise</corr>
                  </choice>, whereof<lb/>
comes not <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>*<notvariant>ome</notvariant></sic>
                     <corr>some</corr>
                  </choice> good to my <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>*el*e *<notvariant>nd</notvariant></sic>
                     <corr><normalised orig="selfe" auto="true">self</normalised> and</corr>
